[1] Saudi Arabia, 16 new cases, 5 deaths - MOH 14 May 2014
Date: 14 May 2014
Source: Saudi MOH [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CoronaNew/PressReleases/Pages/mediastatement-2014-05-14-001.aspx


MOH: 16 New Confirmed Corona Cases Recorded - 14 May 2014
-------------------------------
Daily Report on the Coronavirus (MERS-CoV) As of 12 pm Local Time in Makkah on Wednesday, [14 May 2014]

The total number of confirmed cases over the past 24 hours: 16 cases
Recovered and discharged cases that previously tested positive and are now negative: 3 cases
The total number of deaths: 5 cases (2 cases were recorded over the past 24 hours, and the other 3 are from previously confirmed cases.)

Overview of the Health Status of the Cases:
- 5 stable cases
- 3 cases without symptoms
- 6 cases in the ICU
- 2 deaths

Health situation of the cases in detail:
A. Riyadh:
- A 31-year-old woman developed respiratory symptoms on [ 11 May 2014]. Her condition is stable.
- A 60-year-old woman suffering from lung problems and a gallbladder infection was admitted to a government hospital on [9 May 2014]. She underwent surgery on [10 May 2014]. She was moved to the ward on [12 May 2014]. Then, she had a heart attack and was transferred to the ICU. She passed away on [13 May 2014].
- A 63-year-old woman was admitted to a government hospital on [22 Apr 2014]. She was diagnosed with liver problems. She developed respiratory symptoms on [9 May 2014]. She passed away on [13 May 2014].
- A 72-year-old man suffering from diabetes, high blood pressure, and kidney failure. He developed respiratory systems and was admitted to a government hospital on [30 Apr 2014]. He tested negative for MERS Corona. On [9 May 2014], his condition deteriorated rapidly. He tested positive for MERS Corona. He is in the ICU.
- A 55-year-old woman suffering from diabetes, high blood pressure, and asthma. She developed respiratory symptoms and was admitted to a government hospital on [12 May 2014]. She is in the ICU.
- A 41-year-old woman who has been in contact with a confirmed case. She does not have any symptoms.
- A 71-year-old man, suffering from diabetes and heart disease, was admitted to a government hospital on [1 Apr 2014] due to diabetic foot. He developed respiratory symptoms on [26 Apr 2014]. He was transferred to the ICU on [5 May 2014] with respiratory symptoms.
- A 23-year-old woman developed respiratory symptoms and was admitted to a government hospital on [21 Apr 2014]. She was transferred to another government hospital on [13 May 2014]. She is in the ICU.
- A 40-year-old woman. She has been in contact with a confirmed case and does not have any symptoms.

B. Jeddah:
- A 42-year-old woman developed respiratory symptoms on [30 Apr 2014]. She was admitted to a government hospital on [1 May 2014]. She is in a stable condition.
- A 53-year-old woman developed respiratory symptoms on [21 Apr 2014]. She was admitted to a private hospital on [22 Apr 2014]. She is in the ICU.
- A 57-year-old man developed respiratory symptoms and was admitted to a private hospital on [7 May 2014]. His condition is stable.
- A 43-year-old man went to a government hospital due to a fever. He tested positive for MERS Corona. His condition is stable.
- A 36-year-old woman developed respiratory symptoms on [8 May 2014]. She was admitted to a government hospital on [11 May 2014]. Her condition is stable.

C. AlMadinah:
- A 2-year-old child with congenital anomalies developed respiratory symptoms on [19 Apr 2014]. She was admitted to a government hospital on [25 Apr 2014]. She is in the ICU.
- A 41-year-old woman who has been in contact with a confirmed case. She does not have any symptoms.

Deaths from previously reported cases:
- A 55-year-old man passed away on [13 May 2014]. He was previously recorded as a confirmed case in Jeddah.
- A 57-year-old man passed away on [13 May 2014]. He was previously recorded as a confirmed case in Jeddah.
A 60-year-old woman passed away on [13 May 2014]. He was previously recorded as a confirmed case in Riyadh.

Recovered and discharged cases that previously tested positive and are now negative:
- A 42-year-old woman was discharged from a government hospital in Jeddah.
- A 56-year-old man, who was in home isolation in Madina, now tested positive for MERS Corona.
- A 58-year-old woman was discharged from a government hospital.

