<promed@promedmail.org>

[With the addition of these 15 newly confirmed cases including 5 deaths, the number of laboratory confirmed MERS-CoV infected cases in Saudi Arabia since June 2012 is 511 including 157 deaths. Four of the 15 newly confirmed cases had been admitted to a hospital for underlying co-morbidities prior to the onset of MERS-CoV consistent symptoms suggesting transmission of the MERS-CoV had occurred in the hospital setting. Three of the newly confirmed infections are reported as asymptomatic. Of note, one of the newly confirmed cases in Madina had been in home isolation, presumably as a MERS-CoV negative contact of a known MERS-CoV infected individual who then tested positive for the MERS-CoV. Of note: 7 of the 15 newly reported MERS-CoV infected individuals were in between 25 and 44 years of age; one wonders how many of these individuals might be healthcare workers in the hospital system.

A map showing the geographic locations of the newly confirmed cases and deaths can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]

